      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t know why ncsi_util.cpp never got converted to lg2.  We should probably make that consistent.\n\n\u003e Need LG2_FORCE_STDERR\u003d1 and 2\u003e\u00261 , and then I can grep version.\n\nI get how awkward that is and as written it is currently expected.\n\nMaybe we should add a method into phosphor-logging where an application can explicitly force stdout?  For a utility like ncsi-netlink, when we call with `--info` we can make that settings change.\n\nGenerally we want most of the code to be using lg2.  It does seem like `printInfo` is explicitly intended to be consumed by humans or scripts (and not a debug routine that is used by long running daemons) so maybe there isn\u0027t much harm in it always going to cout, other than the inconsistency.",
